image.asymptote:
// 3-D interactive (WebGL) figure.
import graph3; size(9cm); currentprojection=orthographic(5,2.6,3);
real f(pair p){return 1+0.35*sin(1.1*p.x)-0.12*(p.y-1.5)^2;}
surface s=surface(f,(0,0),(3,3),24,24);
draw(s, rgb(0.6,0.78,0.95)+opacity(0.55), meshpen=rgb(0.4,0.5,0.7)+linewidth(0.15pt));
real u0=1.2,v0=1.1; triple P=(u0,v0,f((u0,v0)));
triple ru=(1,0,0.385*cos(1.1*u0)), rv=(0,1,-0.24*(v0-1.5));
real a=0.95;
path3 par=P--(P+a*ru)--(P+a*ru+a*rv)--(P+a*rv)--cycle;
draw(surface(par), rgb(0.95,0.8,0.4)+opacity(0.6)); draw(par, black+0.4pt);
draw(P--(P+a*ru), blue+linewidth(1.4pt), Arrow3); label("$\mathbf r_u$", P+a*ru, S);
draw(P--(P+a*rv), heavygreen+linewidth(1.4pt), Arrow3); label("$\mathbf r_v$", P+a*rv, E);
triple n=cross(ru,rv); n=0.9*n/abs(n);
draw(P--(P+n), red+linewidth(1.4pt), Arrow3); label("$\mathbf r_u\times\mathbf r_v$", P+n, N);
dot(P);
draw(O--(3.4,0,0),gray,Arrow3); draw(O--(0,3.4,0),gray,Arrow3); draw(O--(0,0,2.2),gray,Arrow3);
label("$x$",(3.4,0,0),S); label("$y$",(0,3.4,0),E); label("$z$",(0,0,2.2),N);

statement.p:
A thin cylindrical shell has radius 2 and height 5. Its density depends on height: \sigma(x,y,z)=1+\frac{z}{10}\qquad \text{kg/m}^2. Using \mathbf r(\theta,z)=(2\cos\theta,2\sin\theta,z), we have dS=2\,d\theta\,dz. Therefore
M \amp= \int_0^{2\pi}\int_0^5 \left(1+\frac{z}{10}\right)2\,dz\,d\theta \amp= \int_0^{2\pi}\left[2z+\frac{z^2}{10}\right]_0^5\,d\theta \amp= \int_0^{2\pi}\frac{25}{2}\,d\theta \amp= 25\pi.
So the total mass is \boxed{M=25\pi\text{ kg}.}
